result.execSummary:
The defendant Dominique R Williams was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Scanned:  State Subpoena and Certificate of Service.

Defendant Dominique R Williams in court with attorney Danielle Louise Shelton.  Micha Schwab appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: AMI

As to Count 1: 
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY as to Count 1.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty. Judgment of conviction entered.

As to Count 2:
Pursuant to negotiations and on Motion of the State, Count 2 is dismissed and read in for sentencing. 

Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing.  
Court sentenced the defendant to serve 75 days in the House of Correction with credit for 6 days served. 
 Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 12 months with the following conditions:
- Serve 20 days in the House of Correction; STAYED pending review on May 20, 2016 at 1:30 p.m.
- No contact with victim unless approved by the court. Third party contact as allowed by the agent for contact with the child.
- Obtain/maintain employment.
- No contact with firearms.
- Pay DV surcharge plus all other costs and surcharges, including DNA surcharge and restitution if ordered, bail on deposit, if any, to apply; remainder to be paid during the period of probation or a civil judgment will be issued.
- Pay supervision fees.
- Court set restitution at zero.

The defense requests consideration for expungement. Court denies the request. Defendant is NOT eligible for expungement.
